One situation where poor digital communication caused a problem can occur when a student sends an informal or unclear email to a professor.
For example, a student might send a message without a proper subject line, greeting, or explanation, such as “Send marks quickly.” 
This type of message can appear rude or unprofessional and may create a negative impression. 
It may also lead to misunderstandings because the professor does not clearly understand the student’s request.
This situation could have been avoided by following proper email etiquette. The student should include a clear subject line, a respectful greeting,
and a polite explanation of the request. Writing a structured and professional email helps communicate the message clearly and shows respect for the recipient.
Proper digital communication is important because it helps maintain professionalism and prevents unnecessary misunderstandings.
